section.def:
occupier (佔用人) includes
            any number of persons and a body corporate and, in the case of any manufacture, includes
            any person carrying on such manufacture;

paragraph.content:
any other description of vessel in Hong Kong or in the waters of Hong Kong not
used in navigation or not constructed or adapted for use in navigation;
(Replaced 4 of 2002 s. 2 and E.R. 5 of 2021)

the application of this Ordinance to any
                    substances,
                    materials and articles whatsoever;

paragraph.continued:
by reference generally or by reference to any circumstances as may be
                    specified and subject to such terms and conditions as may be specified;
                        (Replaced 4 of 2002 s. 4 and E.R. 5 of 2021)

paragraph.content:
the control of the blasting of stone, earth or other material, the
                    precautions to be taken while such blasting takes place and the times during
                    which such blasting may take place;

subparagraph.content:
by reason of a contravention of or a failure to comply with, whether by
                        act or omission, this Ordinance or regulations made under this Ordinance;
                        or

paragraph.content:
compliance with a provision of a code found by the court to be relevant to
                    a matter to which a contravention or failure alleged in the proceedings
                    relates;

enter and search any place or building in which such officer may have
                    reasonable grounds for suspecting that there may be anything which, under
                    paragraph (e), is liable to seizure;

remove by force any material obstruction to, or any persons obstructing any
                    arrest, detention, search, inspection, seizure or removal which he is empowered
                    to make;

detain any person found in any place or building which he is empowered to
                    enter and search until such place or building has been
                    searched;

the empowering of any public officer to give such directions as he thinks
                    fit for the purposes of the proper control and management and the safety of
                    depots;
